自焚事件發生在潘廷逢大道和黎文悅道十字路口交界的柬埔寨大使館門前。[20]釋廣德和兩個和尚一同步出轎車。之後，他們一個在路中央放置坐墊，另一個拿出五加侖汽油。在示威的僧人圍繞着他排成一圈後，釋廣德以傳統佛教盤腿打坐方式坐在坐墊上。當他的助手把汽油淋在他身上時，他一直在旋轉着念珠並當眾吟誦南無阿彌陀佛（Nam Mô A Di Đà Phật），然後點火。火焰燒着了他的袈裟和身體，並冒出黑煙。

大約十分鐘後，已經燒得焦黑的釋廣德遺體倒在了街上，火熄滅了。一班和尚用黃色的罩袍蓋住了冒煙的屍體，然後嘗試把它放進棺木中，但奇怪的是，他的四肢竟不能屈曲。所以在把遺體運送回西貢市中心的舍利寺時，他的一隻手突出了棺材。在寺院外面，學生們展示著用兩種語言寫的橫額：「一名僧人為了我們的五個訴求而死了！（A Buddhist priest burns himself for our five requests！）」

My friend Amy was born in 1995. She married Ken, her boyfriend from Tinder. A pastor married them at Rosewood hotel. She honours her parents. She's thankful for what her parents have done for her. Her brother is also a good don while her sis needs to be a better daughter. In the east teachers and parents stress the importance of filial piety which means Chinese parental respect. They teach that you should honour your parents and take care of them. Recently Amy's cousin has stolen her watch. It was a question of honour to tell her about it. My brother felt honour bound to tell her too. Her dad is a man of honour and high integrity. Both of us are kickboxing fans. In march fred will be fighting chris for the honour of his country. Winning the championship is a matter of personal honour, family honour and national honour. Recently his church held a banquet in honour of Fred. Amy asked me if I could do her the honour of accompanying her to the banquet which I did. It was a signal honour to meet fred. Fred said humbly "it's a great honour to have you here Amy" We asked him if he would do us the honour of becoming our kickboxing coach. He said "we'll have to see" A couple of waiters did the honours and greeted the guests at the door. After we sat down Fred asked the waitress "will you do the honours and cut us a piece of chicken?" Fred said to us "I would be honoured if you could come and see my fight in march" We gave him an affirmative response. Last year the chairman told fred "I would be honoured if you attended the hall of fame ceremony" which he did. He was honoured for his performance in his last fight. Besides winning the championship in the fight he was honoured with an award for.excellence in grappling. His great grandfather accepted a commission as a senior officer. He was buried with full military honours. By the way some people bought front row tickets at half price or less due to a computer problem but the company said they would honour these tickets nevertheless which could cost over five hundred thousand dollars in lost earnings. His uncle was broke several years ago as he bet the farm on his company which went bankrupt later. He managed to honour his debts in three years. I've read in the newspapers that some customers were promised to get their money back if they weren't satisfied with the products. Later they found they'd been sold down the river as so far they have been unable to contact the scammer. The swindler didn't honour the contracts. Amy is a rabbit lover. In accordance with animal law in hokkaido if your pet is a social animal you must have at least two of them living together. Most citizens honour it.

replies.msg: 生活好忙碌，返到屋企仲要執屋？
很多人可能覺得跟家人前往日本旅遊只能選擇跟團，不過只要旅遊行程規劃得完善一些，一樣可以讓全家人玩得很盡興。
第一次帶爸媽來日本自由行，前往富士山周邊旅遊可以說是最佳選擇！不僅能擺脫都市的擁擠人潮，還能放慢腳步欣賞富士山河口湖風光，遊歷周邊的觀光景點，絕對能讓爸媽玩得開心，還能一圓在富士山打卡的夢。下榻溫泉旅館，一邊欣賞富士山的壯麗景觀，一邊享受溫泉的潤澤，人生的極致享受莫過於此。
想帶爸媽遊覽日本大自然風景，或是前往溫泉鄉泡湯享受人生，都絕對少不了經濟實惠又便利的JR鐵路周遊券。現在，購買平台任一款西日本鐵路周遊券，立即送出1萬日圓的溫泉旅館禮券，限量加碼50名，趕緊將爸媽的份一起購買更划算！
日本有許多適合親子同遊的滑雪場，除了有專門給初學者的滑道，還設有兒童專用的玩雪設施，大人小孩都可以玩翻一整天。富士山滑雪度假村Yeti位於富士山2合目，不僅可遠眺富士山雪景，一覽駿河灣的絕美景致，還擁有適合闔家遊玩的豐富遊樂設施，可以說是親子旅遊的最佳選擇。
從東京出發僅需1小時即可抵達。專為初雪者以及兒童設計的滑雪路線相當豐富，即使不滑雪，也能前往Kid’s Park兒童雪上樂園，享受親子玩雪的樂趣。現在輸入優惠碼即可9折預定輕井澤王子大飯店，週末限定優惠千萬別錯過！
旅行不再是走馬看花，帶孩子一起參與當地的特色活動，不僅能一起體驗新鮮事物，還能深度認識日本文化，讓旅行更加豐富有趣！

閤家同樂：體驗製作廣島美食「廣島燒」
全家人一起動手製作廣島代表美食「廣島燒」，好吃又好玩還有武士風格的頭巾及圍裙可以帶回家。

大啖美食：漁船遊覽．牡蠣小屋BBQ體驗
帶小朋友搭乘漁船遊覽，並前往享用廣島特產的牡蠣等海鮮BBQ。之後前往參拜被列入世界遺產的宮島嚴島神社。

海上兜風賞景：水上自行車體驗
全家人一起搭乘水上自行車穿過豐北町角島大橋下，欣賞絕美景緻。全程體驗過程會用空拍機拍攝後，編輯並加上背景音樂，製作成回憶送給您。

replies.msg: My friend Jason was born in 1995. He married Amy recently, his girlfriend from high school. They will be going to Osaka for their honeymoon. They'll be attending a pageant there. I would've thought that Aiko is highly likely to enter thr final round. Jason said too "My bet is Fumi will enter the final round" My friend Alex has got a commission to compose a waltz for the pageant as one if the contestants will be showcasing her waltz dance which we all can't wait to see. I would like to extend my congratulations to him for receiving a commission for a waltz from the pageant since it's a rare opportunity. I too endorse the congratulations to my friend Kawai on having progressed through the preliminary round. She's a contestant in the beauty contest and I won't be surprised if she progresses through the semifinal. I remember a decade ago there was a protest where the protestors clashed with the police in osaka. I saw it on NHK then. I thought the police weren't tough enough. All the riot police were holding a shield in one hand and a nightstick in the other hand. In this way you can't really fight the protestors and arrest them since you have no free hands to grab ahold of them. That's why it took four policemen to catch ahold of one demonstrator. From a fighting standpoint some of the riot police should be holding just a shield, some just a truncheon, the other both. And all of them should be trained on how they fight when they're holding just a baton, holding just a shield and holding both. It was complete chaos. I didn't think osaka had ever been so chaotic before. The police who I wholeheartedly supported only used tear smoke in an attempt to disperse the demonstrators away which was clearly not enough. The police shouldn't have been afraid of being criticized for using excessive force because it was utterly not the case. Firing rubber bullets and bean bags at the protestors was necessary, lawful and appropriate. Those who sabotaged the nearby buildings and the railings should've been put in jail.
